<h1>Problem 634 - 2017 IMO, P5 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>An integer \(N \ge 2\) is given. A collection of \(N(N + 1)\) soccer players, no two of whom are of the same height, stand in a row. Sir Alex wants to remove \(N(N - 1)\) players from this row leaving a new row of \(2N\) players in which the following \(N\) conditions hold:
<br><br>
(\(1\)) no one stands between the two tallest players,
<br>
(\(2\)) no one stands between the third and fourth tallest players,
<br>
\(\;\;\vdots\)
<br>
(\(N\)) no one stands between the two shortest players.
<br><br>
Show that this is always possible.</p>
